definition.value: A lysophosphatidylcholine in which the remaining acyl group (position not specified) contains 26 carbons and 1 double bond.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (R)-3-hydroxyhexanoic acid.
A fatty amide that is the carboxamide derived from palmitic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z,14Z,17Z,20Z)-hexacosatetraenoic acid.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 2'-O-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 2'-O-methyluridine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A phosphatidylcholine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are (9Z)-hexadecenoyl and (13Z,16Z)-docosadienoyl respectively.
A zwitterionic group derived from N(7)-methylguanosine 5'-phosphate.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of N(2)-methylguanosine 5'-monophosphate residue
A phosphatidylcholine O-38:0 in which the alkyl and acyl groups (located at positions 1 and 2 respectively) are octadecyl and icosanoyl.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 5-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as octadecanoyl and (7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z)-docosatetraenoyl respectively.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-3-oxooctacosatetraenoic acid.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of N(3)-methylpseudouridine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (11Z)-octadecenoyl and (13Z,16Z)-docosadienoyl respectively.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (13Z,16Z,19Z,22Z)-octacosatetraenoic acid.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-nafenopin. It is a peroxisome proliferator that is used experimentally to promote liver tumors. It has been used as an hypolipidemic agent.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as (6Z,9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadecatetraenoyl and (15Z)-tetracosenoyl respectively.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of N(1)-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A dipeptide composed of 3-{[(2E)-4-methoxy-4-oxobut-2-enoyl]amino}alanine and L-phenylalanine joined by peptide linkages.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of N(6),N(6)-dimethyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside that is a pyrimidine ribonucleoside in which the hydroxy group at the 5' position is replaced by a hydrogen.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 2'-O-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate residue.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-3-oxotriacontatetraenoic acid.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of 2-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate residue.

A pyrimidinemonocarboxylic that is orotic acid which is substituted by fluorine at position 5. It is used in yeast molecular genetics to detect expression of the URA3 gene, which encodes orotine-5'-monophosphate dicarboxylase. A yeast with and active URA3 gene converts 5-fluoroorotic acid to fluorodeoxyuridine, which is toxic to cells.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-triacontatetraenoic acid.

A monohydroxyquinoline that is quinolin-8-ol which is substituted by a methyl group at position 2 and by chlorine at positions 5 and 7. An antifungal and antibacterial, it was formerly used for topical treatment of skin conditions and vaginal infections.
A dipeptide composed of 3-{[(2E)-4-methoxy-4-oxobut-2-enoyl]amino}alanine and L-tyrosine joined by peptide linkages.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of N(3)-methyluridine 5'-monophosphate residue.
An inositol phosphoceramide(1-) in which the acyl group is not hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is not hydroxylated at position 4. Major species at pH 7.3.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-3-oxodotriacontatetraenoic acid.
An inositol phosphoceramide in which the acyl group is not hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is not hydroxylated at position 4.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of N(4)-methylcytidine 5'-monophosphate residue.
An inositol phosphoceramide(1-) in which either the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 or the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4. Major species at pH 7.3.
An organic anionic group that is the conjugate base of  5-carboxymethylaminomethyluridine 5'-monophosphate residue.
A  dipeptide composed of 3-{[(2E)-4-methoxy-4-oxobut-2-enoyl]amino}alanine and L-valine joined by peptide linkages.

A tertiary amine in which the nitrogen is substituted by methyl, alpha-naphthylmethyl, and (1E)-cinnamyl groups. It is used (usually as its hydrochloride salt) for the treatment of fungal skin infections.
Any alkaloid based on a carbazole skeleton.
An organic anionic group that is the conjugate base of 5-carboxymethylaminomethyl-2'-O-methyluridine 5'-monophosphate residue.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontatetraenoic acid.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of N(2),N(2)-dimethylguanosine 5'-phosphate residue.

A  monocarboxylic acid amide resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 6-aminonicotinic acid with ammonia. An inhibitor of the NADP(+)-dependent enzyme, 6-phosphogluconate dehydrogenase, it interferes with glycolysis, resulting in ATP depletion and synergizes with DNA-crosslinking chemotherapy drugs, such as cisplatin, in killing cancer cells.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z)-3-oxotetratriacontatetraenoic acid.
A member of the class of  adenosines that is adenosine with the hydrogen on the 5'-hydroxy group replaced with a propanoyl group.
Any substance which is used to reduce or control weight.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z)-tetratriacontatetraenoic acid.
